The article discusses a recent focus by the White House on making college more affordable for Americans. President Obama plans to take executive action to make federal student loan repayments more affordable for nearly 5 million borrowers. The President is also urging Congress to do their part by passing the Senate Democrats' bill to help young people save by refinancing their federal student loans. The article also mentions that Secretary of Education, Arne Duncan, believes that a college education is the single-most important investment that Americans can make to build a stronger future. He acknowledges that college is expensive and that students and families are burdened by student loan debt. Secretary Duncan hopes that the President's actions will make college more affordable and manageable for students and families.